Video demo at https://streamable.com/1dswuq

compile with g++ -lncurses

USAGE:

./lcs [filename]

LCS (Library Cataloguing Software) was a project for CSC211. 

In this project, I:
   
   - Learned basic file I/O and text processing
   
   - Overcomplicated things by a factor of 10 by choosing to roll my own TUI. This required me to:
   
      -  Figure out scalable menus,
      
      -  Implement text wrapping,
      
      -  Implement all user-UI interaction logic for all contexts
      
      -  Implement real-time text drawing (backspacing was a pain)
      
   I just think TUI programs are really cool and like doing stuff from scratch, hence the beyond-scope-of-assignment project.
   
   Project screen mockup:

